---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { TWITTER_HANDLE } from '../consts';
---

<Base title="About">
  <article class="article">
    <header>
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <blockquote>
        Hanlon's razor: "Never attribute to malice that which is adequately explained by
        stupidity."
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        A fine rule, right up until you read the postmortem, and then the internal emails, and then
        the second set of internal emails. This blog operates under the inverse: some things that
        look like incompetence are incompetence, and some things that look like incompetence had a
        product manager, a quarterly target, and a legal review.
      </p>
      <p>
        Expect writing about security, incentives, systems that fail in suspiciously profitable
        ways, and the occasional grudging admission that sometimes it really was just a typo.
      </p>
      <p>
        The short-form version of all this lives at
        <a href={`https://twitter.com/${TWITTER_HANDLE}`}>@{TWITTER_HANDLE}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
